⸻

Minutes of Meeting

Topic: Permission Set & Role creation for Terraform OIDC Service Catalog Product (EKS)
Date: April 6, 2026
Attendees: Sandeep, Alberto, Amar, Suyin, Dan, Raman, Pratik, Veera, Anshul (referenced)

⸻

1. Context / Problem
	•	Team is moving Terraform workspaces to OIDC authentication (removing static AWS keys).
	•	A Service Catalog product already exists to create the Terraform OIDC deployment role for workload accounts.
	•	Currently, not all team members have PowerUser role across accounts.
	•	Need a least-privilege permission set allowing team members to launch the Service Catalog product without granting full PowerUser access.
	•	Goal: enable EKS team to rollout OIDC role across consumer workload accounts.

⸻

2. Key Discussion Points

2.1 PR Update Required
	•	Repository contains policy template for permission set.
	•	Action required:
	•	Clone repository
	•	Add required policy updates
	•	Create Pull Request
	•	Role naming convention to follow format suggested by Daniel.
	•	Specific change:
	•	Copy policy block from lines 79–110
	•	Replace role name at line 84
	•	Do not include tag section.

⸻

2.2 Purpose of Role

The new role will:
	•	Allow launching Service Catalog product
	•	Product creates Terraform OIDC deployment role
	•	Scope limited to:
	•	No broad EKS admin permissions
	•	Only required privileges to launch the Service Catalog product

Key principle:

Follow least privilege access instead of giving PowerUser role to all team members.

⸻

2.3 Tiered Access Discussion

Discussion on whether permission should fall under Tiered Access model.

Options discussed:
	•	Tier 3 → considered too broad
	•	Tier 2 → more appropriate because:
	•	Role does NOT create EKS clusters
	•	Only launches Service Catalog product
	•	Decision leaning:
	•	Allow Tier 2 or higher access
	•	Keep flexible for future migration to tiered access model

⸻

2.4 Why manual launch vs automation?

Question raised:
Why not automate creation of OIDC role automatically?

Current constraints:
	•	Each account may have:
	•	different Terraform workspace name
	•	different project mapping
	•	Not all accounts currently migrated to OIDC
	•	Automation planned in later phase once baseline OIDC roles exist.

Future vision:
	•	Fully automated provisioning
	•	Triggered when cluster provisioning workflow runs (Nova/self-service model)

⸻

2.5 Service Catalog Product Inputs

Parameters required for Service Catalog product:
	•	Terraform organization name
	•	workspace/project identifiers

Used to create:
Terraform deployment role with required policies.

⸻

2.6 Permission Set Creation Process

Steps identified:

Step 1 – Create Permission Set

Sandeep to:
	•	create new permission set
	•	attach required policy
	•	map to AD group

Step 2 – Add Launch Access

Launch permissions must be added to Service Catalog portfolio.

Two options:
	1.	via AWS Console
	2.	via pipeline configuration (preferred)

Pipeline location:
Service Catalog product repo → pipeline configuration → launch constraint section.

Add:
new permission set ARN to launch constraint configuration.

⸻

2.7 AD Group Requirement

Permission set must be mapped to AD group.

Potential users requiring access:
	•	Sandeep
	•	Raman
	•	Dan
	•	Pratik
	•	Veera
	•	Anshul

Action:
confirm existing AD group for EKS squad or create temporary group.

⸻

2.8 Account Targeting Strategy

Need clarity on which accounts should receive role.

Initial scope:
Non-production workload accounts.

Possible targeting options:
	•	account IDs list
	•	account grouping construct

Examples of group identifiers:
	•	broad-workload-all
	•	nonprod-workload-asia
	•	other predefined account groupings created by platform team.

Need confirmation from Sherman/Dan on correct group.

